{
  "texts": [
    "(We have equality in Step 1 since D ad = 1 2 β + ad, so the flow of X = X V preserves H.) Hence, their restriction to a given fibre of π: M → B commutes with the monodromy.",
    "This will force the modromy to consist of automorphisms by Lemma A.6.Fix b ∈ B.",
    "By Steps 3 and 4, the fibre M b = π -1 (b) with the vector field X| M b is a nilsoliton for the induced metric.",
    "In particular, there is a p ∈ M b such that X p = 0 by Proposition A.4.",
    "If γ is the horizontal lift of a closed curve representing γ ∈ π 1 (B) beginning at q ∈ M b, then η t • γ is a horizontal lift starting from η t (q)."
